Comments.Message:
I added the missed resources to UIComponents folder. But I guess you still have to change the code in:
TaskEditor\UIComponents\DailyTriggerUI.Designer.cs;
TaskEditor\UIComponents\WeeklyTriggerUI.Designer.cs; and
TaskEditor\UIComponents\MonthlyTriggerUI.Designer.cs.

where you have to bind the Text of the labels to the keys in the resources files. For example, you have to add to InitializeComponent() method the following:

            System.ComponentModel.ComponentResourceManager resources = new System.ComponentModel.ComponentResourceManager(typeof(DailyTriggerUI));

            resources.ApplyResources(this.dailyDaysLabel, "dailyDaysLabel");


Now the Text properties have hard-coded, like: this.dailyDaysLabel.Text = "days";
